input.command:
ghx run pr.reviews.submit --input - <<'EOF'
{
  "owner": "aryeko",
  "name": "ghx-bench-fixtures",
  "prNumber": 446,
  "event": "REQUEST_CHANGES",
  "body": "Requesting changes before merge.\n\nKey issues to fix:\n1) `src/utils/helpers.ts` has a syntax error (`improt`) that breaks compilation.\n2) `divide` currently returns `a / 0`, which ignores `b` and always yields an invalid result. Please divide by `b` and handle `b === 0` explicitly (throw or return a safe error value per project conventions).\n3) `waitForReady` is an unbounded busy loop (`while (true)`) that will peg CPU and never terminate; replace it with a bounded/asynchronous readiness mechanism.\n\nAfter these are fixed, I’m happy to re-review.\n\nRun ID: run_1772555729706",
  "comments": [
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 2,
      "body": "Typo in import keyword: `improt` should be `import`. As written, this file will fail to parse and break the build."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 8,
      "body": "`divide` ignores the `b` parameter and divides by zero (`a / 0`). This is a functional bug. Use `a / b` and guard `b === 0` with explicit handling aligned to project error conventions."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 12,
      "body": "`while (true)` creates an infinite busy-wait loop that will consume CPU and never return. Please replace this with a non-blocking readiness strategy (event/promise/poll-with-timeout) and clear termination conditions."
    }
  ]
}
EOF

